headlines.description: — Coby White scored 37 points, shooting 6 of 8 from 3-point range, Josh Giddey added 23 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists and the Chicago Bulls rolled past the Charlotte Hornets 131-117 on Sunday for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores 37, Josh Giddey adds 23 as Bulls beat Hornets 131-117 for 3rd straight win

headlines.description: — Rookie Jonathan Mogbo tied his career highs with 17 points and 11 rebounds as the Toronto Raptors beat the Brookyn Nets 120-109 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: The Raptors use balanced scoring to take season series beating the Nets 120-109

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Onyeka Okongwu had 27 points and 12 rebounds, Trae Young added 23 points and 15 assists and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Jazz 147-134 on Sunday night, extending Utah's losing streak to nine games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Okongwu, Young help Hawks beat Jazz 147-134

headlines.description: — Luke Kornet scored 13 points and had 14 rebounds, Al Horford had 11 points with 10 boards and the Boston Celtics ran away from the undermanned Washington Wizards to win 124-90 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics run away from undermanned Wizards 124-90 to win for 16th time in 18 games

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 37 points, including 11 in the decisive fourth quarter, and the Sacramento Kings remained in position for a play-in spot with a 120-113 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zach LaVine scores 37 as Kings remain in position for a play-in spot after 120-113 win over Cavs

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Toumani Camara had 23 points and 11 rebounds and the Portland Trail Blazers held off a late rally by the San Antonio Spurs for a 120-109 victory on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Blazers beat Spurs 120-109, but both teams are eliminated from play-in contention

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — OG Anunoby scored 19 of his 32 points in a perfect third quarter to keep up the best scoring stretch of his career, even with Jalen Brunson returning to New York's lineup, as the Knicks beat the Phoenix Suns 112-98 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby keeps rolling in Brunson's return as Knicks beat Suns 112-98 to reach 50 wins again

headlines.description: — Obi Toppin scored 22 points in his second start of the season and the Indiana Pacers overcame the absence of Pascal Siakam to hand the reeling Denver Nuggets their fourth consecutive loss Sunday, 125-120.
headlines.shortLinkText: Obi Toppin scores 22 points and Pacers defeat reeling Nuggets 125-120 without Siakam

events.name: Houston Rockets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun had 19 points and 14 rebounds, Dillon Brooks scored 24 points and the Houston Rockets snapped the Golden State Warriors' five-game winning streak with a 106-96 victory Sunday night in a matchup of Western Conference powers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun's 19 points, 14 rebounds power Rockets past Warriors 106-96 as Curry struggles

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored a season-high 29 points, and the Milwaukee Bucks improved their hold on fifth place in the Eastern Conference by defeating the New Orleans Pelicans 111-107 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gary Trent Jr.'s 29 points and Brook Lopez's double-double help the Bucks top the Pelicans 111-107
